Class AbstractLot

java.lang.Object
  AbstractLot
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, Lot
Direct Known Subclasses:
PartLot, ProductLot
public abstract class AbstractLot
extends java.lang.Object
implements Lot, java.io.Serializable

Defines an abstract class for lots in an inventory system. A lot represents a group of items of the same type that were received or manufactured at the same time.

Version:
2009-09
Author:
Franklin University

setItemCost

public void setItemCost(Money cost)
Sets the cost of each product in the lot. All products in a single lot cost the same amount, but the same product in a different lot may have a different cost. The cost varies for different lots because the product may have cost more (or less) to manufacture or to buy from a different supplier.

Specified by:
